  "body": "Currently the `State` object is entirely memory based. This has two major limitations, the size of the state is limited by the size of memory and cannot be preserved after program termination.\r\n\r\nTo solve this I propose to implement a database based `State` implementation. This will be created by calling `open_file_as_state(path)` and will use the file specified by `path` to store state information.",
